    Description
    IllegalIdentifierLengthException
    Use to indicate that the length of the identifier is too long.(> 24)
    IllegalIntegerException
    Use to indicate that the Integer format is illegal.
    IllegalIntegerRangeException
    Use to indicate that the length of the integer is too long.(> 12)
    IllegalOctalException
    Use to indicate that the Octal format is illegal.
    IllegalSymbolException
    Used when meet an unknown character.
    LexicalException
    Use to indicate that a lexical error has occurred.
    MismatchedCommentException
    Use to indicate that the comment is unmatched.
    MissingLeftParenthesisException
    Use to indicate that we met a expression without left parenthesis, but with right parenthesis.
    MissingOperandException
    Use to indicate that we met a expression without an operand.
    MissingOperatorException
    Use to indicate that we met a expression without an operator.
    MissingRightParenthesisException
    Use to indicate that we met a expression without right parenthesis, but with left parenthesis.
    OberonException
    the base exception class for Oberon, all other exceptions should extend this class.
    ParameterMismatchedException
    Use to indicate that when a procedure is called, but the number of parameters is not matched.
    SemanticException
    Use to indicate that we met a semantic error.
    SyntacticException
    Use to indicate that we met a syntactic error.
    TypeMismatchedException
    Use to indicate that the type of two operands are not matched, or in procedure call, the actually parameter type is not matched with the formal parameter type.
